Order under Section 69
Residential Tenancies Act, 2006
  File Number: EAL-12031-10

DC (the 'Landlord') applied for an order to terminate the tenancy and evict DB (the 'Tenant') because the Tenant did not pay the rent that the Tenant owes.
  This application was heard in Ottawa on January 12, 2011.
  The Landlord’s Representative, AM and the Tenant assisted by Duty Counsel, DW attended the hearing.
  At the hearing, the parties acknowledged that the Tenant owes the Landlord $3,818.20.  This amount represents the rental arrears to January 31, 2011 and the cost of filing the application.  The parties also consented to the following order.
  On consent of the parties, it is ordered that:
  1.        The Tenant shall pay the Landlord $3,818.20 and any new rent that becomes due during the following payment plan:
a)     $700.00 for the rental arrears shall be paid on or before January 12, 2011;
b)     $800.00 for the rental arrears shall be paid on or before January 27, 2011;
c)      $800.00 for part of the February 2011 rent shall be paid on or before February 10, 2011;
d)     $800.00 shall be paid on or before February 24, 2011.  This amount represents $154.64 for the remainder of the February 2011 rent and $645.36 for the rental arrears;
e)     $800.00 for part of the March 2011 rent shall be paid on or before March 10, 2011;
f)        $800.00 shall be paid on or before March 24, 2011.  This amount represents $154.64 for the remainder of the March 2011 rent and $645.36 for the rental arrears;
g)     $800.00 for part of the April 2011 rent shall be paid on or before April 7, 2011;
h)      $800.00 shall be paid on or before April 21, 2011.  This amount represents $154.64 for the remainder of the April 2011 rent and $645.36 for the rental arrears;
i)        $1,336.76 shall be paid on or before May 1, 2011.  This amount represents $954.64 for the May 2011 rent and $382.12 for the remainder of the rental arrears and the cost of filing the application.
2.        In the event that the Tenant fails to make any of the above-indicated payments in full and on time, the entire unpaid balance of the amount set out in this order shall become due and payable forthwith under this order. The Landlord shall be entitled to apply to the Board, without notice to the Tenant, no later than thirty (30) days after a breach of this order, for an order terminating the tenancy and evicting the Tenant and for any new arrears, NSF cheque fees and related administrative fees that have become due after the date of this order pursuant to section 78 of the Residential Tenancies Act, 2006.
